{NORTH has 18 points, a doubleton in the opponent's suit, and at least three cards in the unbid suits. 
This is an ideal hand for a Takeout Double. 

SOUTH has good strength in WEST's \D suit, probably two stoppers. 
He has 9 points and no 4-card suit of his own. This is the type of hand to respond 1NT.

NORTH is happy to play Notrump now that she knows the \Ds are covered, 
so she bids 3NT.}

