{SOUTH has an opening hand, 14 points and five \Ss. But EAST beat him to the punch, 
so he overcalls 1\S. 

NORTH also has 14 points, she doesn't care too much for \Ss, but she has an 
excellent stopper in \Hs. 
She jumps to 2NT, inviting SOUTH to bid game.

Since SOUTH has several points more than he might have had, and no 6-card \S suit to rebid, 
he happily bids 3NT.}

